# Node and TypeScript

- Prefer strict TypeScript; avoid `any` without justification.
- Match existing module style (ESM vs CJS) and import paths.
- Use the project's test runner and lint scripts before finishing work.
- Colocate tests near source or follow the repo's test layout.
- Do not commit secrets; use environment variables for configuration.
